Purpose:
To showcase 3 key features of your project clearly on the landing page.

Implementation Guidelines:

Section Placement

Place this section below the Intro Section.

Use a container or a <section> element with an id, e.g., #features.

Feature Items

Each feature should include:

Image / GIF / Video: A visual representation of the feature.

Feature Name: A clear heading, e.g., <h3>Dynamic Header & Footer</h3>

Feature Description: A short paragraph explaining the featureâ€™s purpose.

Example Layout in JSX/HTML:

<section id="features">
  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <div className="feature-list">
    <div className="feature-item">
      <img src="path/to/header-footer.png" alt="Dynamic Header and Footer"/>
      <h3>Dynamic Header & Footer</h3>
      <p>Customize the header and footer across all pages with toggle, color, and logo options.</p>
    </div>
    <div className="feature-item">
      <img src="path/to/page-content.png" alt="Page Content"/>
      <h3>Custom Page Content</h3>
      <p>Add buttons, contact forms, text, and images, and modify their style dynamically.</p>
    </div>
    <div className="feature-item">
      <img src="path/to/project-management.png" alt="Project Management"/>
      <h3>Project & Page Management</h3>
      <p>Create multiple projects and pages, and manage them efficiently in a dynamic interface.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


Styling Tips

Arrange features in a grid or flex layout.

Use consistent sizes for images or GIFs.

Add spacing and subtle hover effects for interactivity.

Deliverable Section:

A visually appealing feature section that clearly explains 3 main functionalities of your project.

Include screenshots or GIFs if required for documentation.
